E-Verify Listens - by IdeaScale | Popular | electronic
Go to the Web Services Campaign

Since 2005 employer agents with an electronic I-9 product have been allowed to use electronic signatures on TNC documents. Having E-Verify provide the TNC document PDFs without electronic signatures is a problem since the employer agents software will now need to figure out how to apply the electronic signatures. Either the employer agent system should generate the TNC documents or E-Verify should generate the TNC documents with electronic signatures. Employers hiring thousands of employees a month will be extremely burdened in a negative way if TNC documents do not contain electronic signatures.
